<br>
VS and the wizzy staff are a similar sort of epic quest bottleneck, according to my understanding.  With two differences that I know of:  the wizzy staff does not always drop, and wizzy epics in not as much demand as rez sticks.<br>
<br>
I haven't weighed the whole thing out with what I would consider to be enough thought, so I'm interested to read people talk about it.<br>
<br>
I do see a couple of interesting advantages to a Ragefire rotations (even though I can not say I think the pros outweigh the cons, please see above paragraph <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
1.)  It addresses somewhat the issue of Draelyn, Aurorelle, and Sagemon insofar as it negates the need to brainlessly camp<br>
2.)  As a trade-off, it does put the squeeze on guilds such as ours who are not rotation capable, BUT becoming rotation-capable is a need and a goal that we have already needed to set long ago, so it really doesn't rock the boat so to speak.  It's just another reason to do what we already knew we had to do.<br>
3.)  It preserves the practice of powerful guilds agreeing among themselves<br>
4.)  It clearly defines what smaller/rising guilds need to do to get where they want to get<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts,<br>
Theo<br>
