<br>
The idea of a rotation isn't going to go very far.  Aside from the fact that a lot of people are fed up with rotations, there are other problems.  Who would be in the rotation?  Are we giving rotation spots to big guilds, and then dumping all of the smaller guilds into a &quot;pickup slot&quot;?  Who decides?<br>
<br>
No one seems to be coming up with any concrete proposals, so I'll toss one out.  Feel free to rip up this proposal as much as you want.  It won't hurt my feelings.  I'd just like to see some movement toward a resolution.<br>
<br>
1. In order to be eligible for Ragefire, a cleric must be level 54 and must have completed the Ixiblat Fer/Overking portion of the epic quest.<br>
<br>
2. After each Ragefire spawn, the eligible clerics who wish to take the next Ragefire spawn identify themselves, and a numbered list is prepared.  Each cleric gets a number in the lottery.<br>
<br>
3. At a prearranged time and place (maybe in WC), a designated person randoms the numbers on the list.  The winning cleric is awarded the next Ragefire spawn.<br>
<br>
4. Camping Ragefire in Skyfire is unnecessary and gives no right to the spawn.  However, the cleric must kill Ragefire within 24 hours of the spawn, or it goes FFA.  This should allow clerics in all time zones to gather the forces necessary to make the kill.<br>
<br>
5. Each time a cleric loses in the lottery, the cleric gets an additional number in the next lottery.  For example, suppose that 25 clerics are in the first lottery.  Someone rolls /ran 1 25, and a winner is chosen.  If the 24 losers all enter the next lottery, they each get two numbers, so they are numbers 1 to 48.  New clerics would get a single number.  After two losses, a cleric would get three numbers, and so forth.  In other words, the longer you are in the lottery system, the greater your chance to win relative to new entries.<br>
<br>
Frankly, I'd probably get my epic sooner under an FFA system than under that system.  I'd be willing to live with this sort of system to eliminate all of the headaches and flames that would accompany an FFA system.  This would be a definite improvement over the idiotic current system. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>
High Priest of Quellious the Tranquil<BR>A Twist of Fate</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uglorianafrostglitter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloriana Frostglitter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1251<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/4/02 2:49:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3108.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is RF a camp or FFA!  Need some advice.</span><hr size=1> Hey, I was just responding to your friendly &quot;notice.&quot;  It was an open threat against the current cleric camping Ragefire who happens to be a beloved member of Affliction.  A person who has already invested 3+ days into the camp.  Do I think the idea of camping 6 days for an outdoor spawn is idiotic? Yes, I do.  Heck, I thought 3 days in Sol B was pretty lame.<br>
