We respect a guild's time to wage battle in a 24 hour window for VS and Trak.  I think this sounds very fair as well.  It also satisfies the need of eliminating the brain-ooze 6-day camp.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
5. Each time a cleric loses in the lottery, the cleric gets an additional number in the next lottery. For example, suppose that 25 clerics are in the first lottery. Someone rolls /ran 1 25, and a winner is chosen. If the 24 losers all enter the next lottery, they each get two numbers, so they are numbers 1 to 48. New clerics would get a single number. After two losses, a cleric would get three numbers, and so forth. In other words, the longer you are in the lottery system, the greater your chance to win relative to new entries.<br>
