<br>
I think of this as very generous, actually.  That a person/guild who tries and fails gets an increased chance at going for it again.  I find it rather ingenious, both as an inspired system and the generosity that inspires such an idea (there is an inherent kindness in increasing the chance of letting someone turn their &quot;loss&quot; into a &quot;win&quot;).  Moreover, it encourages Feldynn's above-posted idea of everyone helping everyone else out.  Such an idea serves to remove the boundaries of guild, and allows the entire community to support a questing cleric in their pursuit.  I have not read anything about a large guild not being eligible to help a smaller guild in any of the proposal.  I really really like this.<br>
<br>
For that same reason, I'd be very surprised if this note was not pushed back by those who are larger and more powerful.  Pleasantly surprised, yes, but surprised nonetheless.<br>
<br>
In closing, Sagemon's proposal is the best idea I've seen.  Of course, that is from where I see things, your mileage may very.  Just my 2cp, take it or leave it.<br>
